<eesti>Ameti&uuml;hingute register </eesti>
<inglise>Register of trade unions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ameti&uuml;hingute register on mittetulundus&uuml;hingute ja sihtasutuste registri osa, mille suhtes kohaldatakse mittetulundus&uuml;hingute ja sihtasutuste registri kohta &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatut, kui k&auml;esolevast seadusest ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The register of trade unions is a part of the non-profit associations and foundations register with regard to which the provisions of legislation concerning the non-profit associations and foundations register apply unless otherwise provided for in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Registrit peetakse ameti&uuml;hingute kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The register shall be maintained concerning trade unions. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Registrit peavad maa- ja linnakohtute registriosakonnad (registripidajad) oma t&ouml;&ouml;piirkonnas asuvate ameti&uuml;hingute kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The registration departments (registrars) of county and city courts shall maintain the register of trade unions located in their jurisdiction. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Registri kanded teeb registripidaja, kelle t&ouml;&ouml;piirkonnas on ameti&uuml;hingu asukoht. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Entries in the register shall be made by the registrar in whose jurisdiction the trade union is located. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Registrisse kandmata j&auml;tmise keeld </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibition on refusal to enter in register </inglise>
<eesti>Kui ameti&uuml;hing vastab k&auml;esoleva seaduse n&otilde;uetele ameti&uuml;hingulise eesm&auml;rgi, asutajate, liikmete, liikmete arvu, ameti&uuml;hinguorganite asutamisotsuste, seadusest tulenevate juhtorganite olemasolu ja p&auml;devuse osas ning kui ameti&uuml;hingu p&otilde;hikirjas on reguleeritud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 8 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uded ning kui ameti&uuml;hingu nimi ei ole eksitav ameti&uuml;hingu p&auml;devuse ulatuse ja &otilde;igusliku vormi osas, ei ole registripidajal &otilde;igust registreerimisest keelduda. </eesti>
<inglise>If a trade union complies with the requirements of this Act regarding the objectives of the trade union, the founders, the members, the number of members, foundation resolutions of trade union bodies, the existence and competence of directing bodies arising from law, and if the articles of association of the trade union regulate the requirements provided for in &sect; 8 of this Act, and if the name of the trade union is not misleading regarding the scope of competence and legal form of the trade union, the registrar does not have the right to refuse registration. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Ameti&uuml;hingute l&otilde;petamine </eesti>
<inglise>Dissolution of Trade Unions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Ameti&uuml;hingu vabatahtlik l&otilde;petamine </eesti>
<inglise>Voluntary dissolution of trade unions </inglise>
<eesti>Ameti&uuml;hing l&otilde;petatakse vabatahtlikult &uuml;ldkoosoleku otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>A trade union is dissolved voluntarily by a resolution of the general meeting. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsuse likvideerimise korra kohta v&otilde;tab &uuml;ldkoosolek vastu vastavalt p&otilde;hikirjale ja seadusele. </eesti>
<inglise>The general meeting shall adopt a resolution on the procedure for liquidation pursuant to the articles of association and law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;petamine kohtu otsusega </eesti>
<inglise>Dissolution by court judgment </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ameti&uuml;hing l&otilde;petatakse kohtu otsusega huvitatud isiku n&otilde;udel, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A trade union is dissolved by a court judgment at the request of an interested person if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ameti&uuml;hingu asutamine v&otilde;i tegevus on vastuolus seaduse v&otilde;i ameti&uuml;hingu p&otilde;hikirjaliste eesm&auml;rkidega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the foundation or activities of the trade union are contrary to law or the objectives of the trade union specified in the articles of association; </inglise>
<eesti>2) liikmete arv on langenud alla k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud arvu ja juhatus ei algata vabatahtlikku l&otilde;petamist kuue kuu jooksul; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the number of members falls below the number provided for in subsection 7 (1) of this Act and the management board does not initiate voluntary dissolution within six months; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ameti&uuml;hingu suhtes on tehtud pankrotiotsus. </eesti>
<inglise>3) a bankruptcy order is made with regard to the trade union. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kohus v&otilde;ib anda t&auml;htaja k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 1 nimetatud puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A court may set a deadline for elimination of deficiencies specified in clause (1) 1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Vara jaotamine </eesti>
<inglise>Distribution of assets </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ameti&uuml;hingu likvideerimise korral jaotatakse p&auml;rast v&otilde;lausaldajate k&otilde;igi n&otilde;uete rahuldamist ja raha deponeerimist allesj&auml;&auml;nud vara vastavalt p&otilde;hikirjale. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon liquidation of a trade union, the assets remaining after satisfaction of all claims of creditors and the deposit of money shall be distributed pursuant to the articles of association. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui p&otilde;hikirjas etten&auml;htud vara jaotamise korda ei ole v&otilde;imalik kohaldada, antakse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud allesj&auml;&auml;nud vara liidule v&otilde;i keskliidule, kuhu likvideeritud ameti&uuml;hing kuulus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If it is not possible to apply the procedure for the distribution of assets pursuant to the articles of association, the remaining assets provided for in subsection (1) of this section shall be transferred to the federation or central federation to which the trade union belongs. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui ameti&uuml;hing ei kuulunud liitu ega keskliitu, jaotatakse allesj&auml;&auml;nud vara sarnase tegevusala v&otilde;i kutseala ameti&uuml;hingutele. </eesti>
<inglise>If a trade union does not belong to a federation or central federation, the remaining assets shall be distributed between the trade unions of a similar area of activity or profession. </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Ameti&uuml;hingute p&auml;devus ja &otilde;igused </eesti>
<inglise>Competence and Rights of Trade Unions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindamise p&otilde;him&otilde;tted </eesti>
<inglise>Principles of representation of employees </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kollektiivsetes t&ouml;&ouml;suhetes on ameti&uuml;hingul oma p&auml;devuse piires &otilde;igus esindada ja kaitsta t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &otilde;igusi ja huve. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In collective employment relationships, trade unions have the right to represent and protect the rights and interests of employees within the limits of their competence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Individuaalsetes t&ouml;&ouml;suhetes esindab ja kaitseb ameti&uuml;hing oma liikmete &otilde;igusi ja huve liikme volituse alusel, kui seadustes ei ole s&auml;testatud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In individual employment relationships, trade unions shall represent and protect the rights and interests of their members on the basis of authorisations from the members unless otherwise provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ameti&uuml;hingul on individuaalsetes t&ouml;&ouml;suhetes &otilde;igus esindada ja kaitsta ameti&uuml;hingu liikmeks mitteoleva t&ouml;&ouml;taja &otilde;igusi ja huve tingimusel, et ta esitab ameti&uuml;hingule vastava kirjaliku volituse. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In individual employment relationships, trade unions have the right to represent and protect the rights and interests of employees who are not members of trade unions provided that the employees submit corresponding written authorisations to the trade unions. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Ameti&uuml;hingute p&auml;devus </eesti>
<inglise>Competence of trade unions </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajate &otilde;iguste ja huvide esindamiseks, teostamiseks ja kaitsmiseks kuulub ameti&uuml;hingute p&auml;devusse: </eesti>
<inglise>In order to represent, exercise and protect the rights and interests of employees, the following is within the competence of a trade union: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kollektiiv- v&otilde;i muude t&ouml;&ouml;-, teenistus- v&otilde;i sotsiaalvaldkonda puudutavate lepingute s&otilde;lmimine t&ouml;&ouml;andjate ja nende &uuml;hendustega, riigiasutuste ning kohalike omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste ja Vabariigi Valitsusega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) entry into collective agreements or other contracts pertaining to employment, service or social affairs with employers or the associations of employees, state agencies, local governments or the Government of the Republic; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &otilde;igusaktide eeln&otilde;udesse ettepanekute esitamine t&ouml;&ouml;tajate t&ouml;&ouml;-, teenistus- ja kutsealaseid ning majanduslikke ja sotsiaalseid &otilde;igusi ja huve puudutavates k&uuml;simustes; </eesti>
<inglise>2) submission of proposals into draft legislation in issues relating to the employment, service-related, professional, economic and social rights and interests of employees; </inglise>
<eesti>3) riigi- ja kohalike omavalitsuste asutustele ettepanekute esitamine t&ouml;&ouml;- ja sotsiaalk&uuml;simusi reguleerivate &otilde;igusaktide t&auml;iendamiseks ja muutmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) submission of proposals to state and local government agencies for the amendment of legislation regulating employment and social issues; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse ja t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu olukorra parandamiseks koost&ouml;&ouml; tegemine vastavate riigi- ja valitsusasutuste ning t&ouml;&ouml;andjate ja nende &uuml;hendustega; </eesti>
<inglise>4) in order to improve the situation of occupational health and safety, co-operation with the corresponding state and government agencies, and employers and their associations; </inglise>
<eesti>5) riigi t&ouml;&ouml;turuasutuste ja kohalike omavalitsustega koost&ouml;&ouml; tegemine t&ouml;&ouml;ga h&otilde;lmatuse, v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe, t&auml;iendkoolituse, kutseoskuse ja erialase ettevalmistuse parandamise k&uuml;simustes; </eesti>
<inglise>5) co-operation with state employment agencies and local governments in issues relating to the improvement of employment, training, in-service training, professional skills and professional training; </inglise>
<eesti>6) osalemine t&ouml;&ouml;tajate konsulteerimisel, informeerimisel ja otsuste tegemisel ulatuses, mis on reguleeritud k&auml;esoleva seaduse, muude &otilde;igusaktide ja kokkulepetega; </eesti>
<inglise>6) participation in the consulting and informing of employees, and in decision-making to the extent which is regulated by this Act, other legislation and agreements; </inglise>
<eesti>7) oma liikmete esindamine ja kaitsmine t&ouml;&ouml;vaidlusorganites, suhetes riigi- ja kohalike omavalitsuste asutuste, t&ouml;&ouml;andjate ja t&ouml;&ouml;andjate &uuml;hendustega. </eesti>
<inglise>7) representation and protection of the members of trade unions in labour dispute resolution bodies, in relations with state and local government agencies, employers and associations of employers. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Ameti&uuml;hingute &otilde;igused </eesti>
<inglise>Rights of trade unions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;devuse teostamiseks on ameti&uuml;hingutel &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to exercise their competence, trade unions have the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) saada t&ouml;&ouml;andjatelt, nende esindajatelt, riigiasutustelt ja kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksustelt takistamatult t&ouml;&ouml;- ja sotsiaalalast informatsiooni ning muud teavet t&ouml;&ouml;tajate huve puudutavates k&uuml;simustes; </eesti>
<inglise>1) receive freely information concerning employment and social affairs and other information concerning issues involving the interests of employees from employers, their representatives, state agencies and local governments; </inglise>
<eesti>2) pidada t&ouml;&ouml;-, teenistus- ja sotsiaalsetes k&uuml;simustes l&auml;bir&auml;&auml;kimisi t&ouml;&ouml;andjate ja nende &uuml;henduste, riigiasutuste ja kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksustega kollektiiv- ja muude lepingute s&otilde;lmimiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) conduct bargaining in employment, service-related and social issues with employers and the associations of employers, state agencies and local governments for entry into collective and other agreements; </inglise>
<eesti>3) esitada ettepanekuid &otilde;igusakti eeln&otilde;u kohta, mis puudutab selle ameti&uuml;hingu (liidu) liikmete t&ouml;&ouml;-, teenistus- ja kutsealaseid ning majanduslikke ja sotsiaalseid &otilde;igusi ja huve; </eesti>
<inglise>3) submit proposals concerning draft legislation relating to the employment, service-related, professional, economic and social rights and interests of members of the trade unions (federations); </inglise>
<eesti>4) saada ameti&uuml;hingu valitud esindaja kaudu teavet riigi t&ouml;&ouml;turuasutustelt t&ouml;&ouml;turu olukorrast, vabadest t&ouml;&ouml;kohtadest ja t&ouml;&ouml;turukoolituse v&otilde;imalustest; </eesti>
<inglise>4) receive information on the situation in the labour market, vacant jobs and possibilities of employment training from state employment agencies through representatives elected by the trade unions; </inglise>
<eesti>5) avaldada oma seisukohti massimeedia kaudu, omada tr&uuml;kibaasi ja massiteabevahendeid, arendada kirjastustegevust, sealhulgas v&auml;lja anda ja levitada ajalehti ning muid tr&uuml;kiseid; </eesti>
<inglise>5) disseminate their positions through mass media, own printing facilities and media, develop publishing, and to issue and distribute newspapers and other printed matter; </inglise>
<eesti>6) oma eesm&auml;rkide saavutamiseks korraldada seadustes etten&auml;htud korras koosolekuid, miitinguid, t&auml;navarongk&auml;ike, pikette ja streike; </eesti>
<inglise>6) in order to achieve their objectives, organise meetings, political meetings, street parades, pickets and strikes pursuant to the procedure prescribed by law; </inglise>
<eesti>7) vabalt arendada p&otilde;hikirjaliste eesm&auml;rkide elluviimiseks mis tahes v&auml;lissuhteid, sealhulgas &uuml;hineda t&ouml;&ouml;tajate rahvusvaheliste organisatsioonidega; </eesti>
<inglise>7) freely develop any kind of foreign relations in order to carry out their objectives specified in the articles of association, including joining international organisations of employees; </inglise>
<eesti>8) koolitada ja n&otilde;ustada oma liikmeid t&ouml;&ouml;-, sotsiaal- ja muudes t&ouml;&ouml;tajate huve puudutavates k&uuml;simustes. </eesti>
<inglise>8) train and consult their members in employment and social issues and other issues involving the interests of employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ameti&uuml;hingutel on &otilde;igus teostada ka muid seadustes v&otilde;i lepingutes etten&auml;htud &otilde;igusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Trade unions have the right to exercise other rights prescribed in Acts or agreements. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Ameti&uuml;hingute suhted t&ouml;&ouml;andjatega </eesti>
<inglise>Relations between Trade Unions and Employers </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja &otilde;igused </eesti>
<inglise>Rights of employees </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;tajal on &otilde;igus kuuluda oma t&ouml;&ouml;kohaj&auml;rgsesse v&otilde;i m&otilde;nda muusse ameti&uuml;hingusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Employees have the right to be members of trade unions of their workplace or other trade unions. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajal on &otilde;igus tegutseda ameti&uuml;hingu valitud esindajana. </eesti>
<inglise>Employees have the right to act as elected members of trade unions. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;taja ja t&ouml;&ouml;otsija &otilde;igusi ei v&otilde;i piirata s&otilde;ltuvalt tema kuulumisest v&otilde;i mittekuulumisest ameti&uuml;hingusse, ameti&uuml;hingu valitud esindajaks olemisest v&otilde;i muust seaduslikust ameti&uuml;hingualasest tegevusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The rights of employees or persons who seek employment shall not be restricted on grounds of their membership in trade unions, on being elected representatives of trade unions or on other legal activities related to trade unions. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud &otilde;iguste piiramise all m&otilde;istetakse ameti&uuml;hingualase tegevuse t&otilde;ttu: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The restriction of rights provided for in subsection (2) of this section means that due to activities related to trade unions: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;le mittelubamist; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an employee is prohibited to work; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;tajaga t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamist v&otilde;i teenistusest vabastamist; </eesti>
<inglise>2) an employment contract of an employee is terminated or he or she is released from service; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste halvendamist; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the working conditions of an employee are impaired; </inglise>
<eesti>4) palga, lisatasude v&auml;hendamist, lisatasude mittemaksmist; </eesti>
<inglise>4) salary or additional remuneration is reduced, additional remuneration is not paid; </inglise>
<eesti>5) distsiplinaarkaristuse m&auml;&auml;ramist; </eesti>
<inglise>5) disciplinary penalties are imposed; </inglise>
<eesti>6) &auml;hvardamist t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamise, teenistusest vabastamise, t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste halvendamise, karistuse m&auml;&auml;ramisega; </eesti>
<inglise>6) an employee is threatened by termination of the employment contract, release from service, impairment of working conditions, imposition of punishment; </inglise>
<eesti>7) muud ebav&otilde;rdset kohtlemist. </eesti>
<inglise>7) an employee is otherwise treated unequally. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;tajal, kelle &otilde;igusi k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud viisil piirati, on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda piiramise l&otilde;petamist, talle tekitatud varalise v&otilde;i mittevaralise kahju h&uuml;vitamist ning endise olukorra taastamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An employee whose rights are restricted in a way provided for in subsection (3) of this section has the right to demand termination of the restriction, compensation for the proprietary and non-proprietary damage caused to him or her and restoration of the former situation. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;andja vabaneb vastutusest &uuml;ksnes siis, kui t&otilde;estab, et t&ouml;&ouml;taja &otilde;iguste piiramine oli seaduslik ega olnud seotud t&ouml;&ouml;taja ameti&uuml;hingualase tegevusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An employer shall be released from liability only if he or she proves that the restriction of the rights of an employee is legal and is not related to the activities of the employee related to trade unions. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustused suhetes ameti&uuml;hinguga </eesti>
<inglise>Obligations of employers in relations with trade unions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer is required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) andma ameti&uuml;hingu juhatusele (usaldusisikule) v&otilde;imaluse korral t&ouml;&ouml;ruumi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) grant a workroom for the management board of a trade union (representative), if possible; </inglise>
<eesti>2) andma v&auml;hemalt kord kuus ruumi ameti&uuml;hingu&uuml;rituste l&auml;biviimiseks ja lubama neile &uuml;ritustele &uuml;hingu, asutuse v&otilde;i muu organisatsiooni ameti&uuml;hingu liikmeid, samuti teisi ameti&uuml;hingute poolt kutsutud isikuid. </eesti>
<inglise>2) grant premises for holding trade union events at least once a month and permit members of the trade union of a company, agency or other organisation and also other persons invited by trade unions to participate in these events. </inglise>
<eesti>Ameti&uuml;hingu poolt v&auml;ljaspool &uuml;hingut, asutust v&otilde;i muud organisatsiooni kutsutud isikute osav&otilde;tust tuleb eelnevalt t&ouml;&ouml;andjale teatada; </eesti>
<inglise>An employer shall be notified in advance of the participation of persons who are invited outside of the company, agency or other organisation by the trade union; </inglise>
<eesti>3) v&otilde;imaldama ameti&uuml;hingu liikmele ameti&uuml;hingu poolt esitatud kirjalike kutsete alusel aastas v&auml;hemalt viis t&ouml;&ouml;st vaba p&auml;eva osalemiseks ameti&uuml;hingu poolt korraldatavas koolituses v&otilde;i ameti&uuml;hingute organite t&ouml;&ouml;s tingimusel, et sellega ei kaasne olulisi takistusi t&ouml;&ouml;andja majandustegevuses. </eesti>
<inglise>3) allow members of a trade union at least five days free from work in order for them to participate in training organised by the trade union or in the work of trade union bodies on the basis of written invitations submitted by the trade union provided that it does not significantly hinder the economic activities of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva punkti alusel antavatel t&ouml;&ouml;st vabadel p&auml;evadel s&auml;ilitatakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajale tema keskmine palk kahe p&auml;eva eest aastas; </eesti>
<inglise>On the days free from work granted pursuant to this clause, the employee shall continue to receive his or her average wages for two days a year; </inglise>
<eesti>4) asuma ameti&uuml;hingu valitud esindaja taotlusel l&auml;bir&auml;&auml;kimistesse kollektiiv- ja muude t&ouml;&ouml;-, teenistus- v&otilde;i sotsiaalvaldkonda puudutava lepingu s&otilde;lmimiseks, t&auml;iendamiseks ning muutmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) at the request of an elected representative of a trade union, commence bargaining for entry into or amendment of collective agreements and other contracts pertaining to employment, service or social affairs; </inglise>
<eesti>5) lubama ameti&uuml;hingu poolt valitud esindajaid takistamatult tutvuda t&ouml;&ouml;tajate t&ouml;&ouml;korralduse ja tingimustega &uuml;hingus, asutuses v&otilde;i muus organisatsioonis, kus t&ouml;&ouml;tab selle ameti&uuml;hingu liikmeid. </eesti>
<inglise>5) permit members elected by a trade union to examine freely the organisation of work and the working conditions in the company, agency or other organisation where members of the trade union are employed. </inglise>
<eesti>Lubama valitud esindajal esitada arvamusi, ettepanekuid t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindamise k&uuml;simustes; </eesti>
<inglise>To permit an elected member to submit opinions and proposals in the issues concerning the representation of employees; </inglise>
<eesti>6) t&auml;itma ameti&uuml;hingute suhtes muid seadustest v&otilde;i kollektiivlepingust tulenevaid kohustusi. </eesti>
<inglise>6) perform other duties arising from law or collective agreements in respect of trade unions. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 loetletud kohustusi v&otilde;ib laiendada kollektiiv- v&otilde;i muu poolte vahel s&otilde;lmitud lepinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The obligations listed in subsection (1) of this section may be extended by a collective agreement or other contract entered into between the parties to the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Ameti&uuml;hingu valitud esindaja kohustused suhetes t&ouml;&ouml;andjaga </eesti>
<inglise>Obligations of elected members of trade unions in relations with employers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ameti&uuml;hingu valitud esindaja on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An elected member of a trade union is required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teatama kirjalikult t&ouml;&ouml;andjale ameti&uuml;hingu asutamisest selles &uuml;hingus, asutuses v&otilde;i muus organisatsioonis hiljemalt kuu aja jooksul, arvates ameti&uuml;hingu asutamiskoosoleku toimumisest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) notify the employer in writing of foundation of a trade union in the company, agency or other organisation not later than within one month after the foundation meeting of the trade union takes place; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teatama kirjalikult t&ouml;&ouml;andjale usaldusisiku ja ameti&uuml;hingu juhatuse liikmete ees- ja perekonnanimed, t&ouml;&ouml;kohad ja volituste kestuse; </eesti>
<inglise>2) notify the employer in writing of the given names and surnames, positions and terms of authority of the representative and the members of the management board of the trade union; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kindlustama t&ouml;&ouml;rahu seaduse ja kollektiivlepinguga m&auml;&auml;ratud ajal; </eesti>
<inglise>3) ensure compliance with the duty to refrain from striking at the time established by law and the collective agreement; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kindlustama kollektiivlepingute t&auml;itmise ameti&uuml;hingul lasuvate kohustuste osas; </eesti>
<inglise>4) ensure the performance of collective agreements in respect of obligations which rest with the trade union; </inglise>
<eesti>5) vahendama vajaduse korral informeerimisel ja konsulteerimisel erinevaid osapooli; </eesti>
<inglise>5) if necessary, mediate between different parties in informing and consulting; </inglise>
<eesti>6) hoidma talle informeerimisel ja konsulteerimisel teatavaks saanud &auml;ri- ja tootmissaladusi ning ametisaladusi; </eesti>
<inglise>6) maintain business, production and professional secrets which become known to him or her during informing or consulting; </inglise>
<eesti>7) tegema koost&ouml;&ouml;d t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna voliniku ja t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna n&otilde;ukoguga t&ouml;&ouml;ohutus- ja t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiualase tegevuse korraldamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>7) co-operate with the working environment representative or working environment council in organisation of the activities related to occupational health and safety; </inglise>
<eesti>8) t&auml;itma t&ouml;&ouml;andja suhtes muid seadustest v&otilde;i kollektiivlepingust tulenevaid kohustusi. </eesti>
<inglise>8) perform other duties arising from law or collective agreements in respect of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 loetletud kohustusi v&otilde;ib laiendada kollektiiv- v&otilde;i muu poolte vahel s&otilde;lmitud lepinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The duties listed in subsection (1) of this section may be extended by a collective agreement or other contract entered into between the parties to the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Ameti&uuml;hingu valitud esindaja osalemine informeerimisel ja konsulteerimisel </eesti>
<inglise>Participation of elected members of trade unions in informing and consulting </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja informeerib &otilde;igeaegselt ameti&uuml;hingu valitud esindajaid: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer shall inform the elected members of a trade union in a timely manner of the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &uuml;hingu, asutuse v&otilde;i muu organisatsiooni majandusaasta p&otilde;hin&auml;itajatest, t&ouml;&ouml;j&otilde;ule tehtavatest kulutustest, olulistest investeeringutest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the basic figures of the financial year, expenses incurred on labour force and significant investments of the company, agency or other organisation; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &uuml;hingu, asutuse, organisatsiooni t&ouml;&ouml;korralduse, tootmise, tehnoloogia, tegevuse p&otilde;hisuundade muutustest; &uuml;hingu, asutuse, organisatsiooni t&auml;htajalistest, osalise t&ouml;&ouml;ajaga t&ouml;&ouml;lepingutest; </eesti>
<inglise>2) changes in the basic objectives of the work organisation, production, technology or activities of the company, agency or organisation; fixed-term and part-time employment contracts of the company, agency or organisation; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &uuml;hingu, asutuse v&otilde;i muu organisatsiooni &uuml;hinemisest, jagunemisest, &uuml;mberkujundamisest, l&otilde;petamisest, ettev&otilde;tte v&otilde;i selle organisatsiooniliselt iseseisva osa &uuml;lemineku korral, struktuuri, haldamisvormi muutustest, p&otilde;hjustest, tagaj&auml;rgedest t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele, kavandatavatest meetmetest; </eesti>
<inglise>3) merger, division, transformation or dissolution of the company, agency or other organisation, upon transfer of the enterprise or an organisationally independent part thereof, of changes in the structure or form of administration, of reasons and consequences of such transfer for the employees, and of devised methods; </inglise>
<eesti>4) muudest t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid ja nende t&ouml;&ouml;d puudutavatest k&uuml;simustest. </eesti>
<inglise>4) other issues pertaining to employees and their work. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Enne vastava otsuse tegemist konsulteerib t&ouml;&ouml;andja eelnevalt ameti&uuml;hingute valitud esindajatega: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Before making a corresponding decision, an employer shall consult the elected representatives of trade unions in advance in the following cases: </inglise>
<eesti>1) majanduslikel p&otilde;hjustel t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel t&ouml;&ouml;tajatega, sealhulgas kollektiivsete koondamiste puhul koondamise p&otilde;hjuse, koondatavate t&ouml;&ouml;tajate v&auml;ljaselgitamise, koondamisega seotud k&uuml;simuste lahendamise, tagaj&auml;rgede leevendamise &uuml;le vastavalt t&ouml;&ouml;seadustes s&auml;testatule; </eesti>
<inglise>1) upon termination of employment contracts with employees for economic reasons; in the event of collective redundancy, on the reasons for redundancy, on identification of employees to be made redundant, on resolution of issues related to redundancy, on mitigating the consequences pursuant to the provisions of labour laws; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;aja ja -re&zcaron;iimi, palgatingimuste, palga maksmise aluste, puhkusegraafiku, t&ouml;&ouml;sisekorraeeskirjade ja teiste suuremat hulka t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid puudutavate t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste muutmisel v&otilde;i kehtestamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) upon changing or establishment of working time and work regimes, wage conditions, bases for payment of wages, holiday schedule, internal work procedure rules and other working conditions which concerns a considerable number of employees; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;tajate t&auml;iend- ja &uuml;mber&otilde;pet, kvalifikatsiooni, t&ouml;&ouml;ohutust ja t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoidu puudutavates k&uuml;simustes; </eesti>
<inglise>3) in issues relating to the in-service training and re-training, qualifications, occupational health and safety of employees; </inglise>
<eesti>4) muudes osapoolte vahel kokku lepitud v&otilde;i seadustes s&auml;testatud k&uuml;simustes. </eesti>
<inglise>4) in other issues agreed between the parties or provided for in Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ameti&uuml;hingu valitud esindaja on kohustatud edastama saadud informatsiooni t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The elected members of trade unions are required to forward the received information to employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ameti&uuml;hingutel on &otilde;igus edastada t&ouml;&ouml;andjale oma arvamus v&auml;hemalt k&uuml;mne p&auml;eva jooksul, kui kokku ei lepita pikemas ajas. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A trade union has the right to forward its opinion to an employer within at least ten days unless a longer period is agreed upon. </inglise>
<eesti>Sel ajal ei ole t&ouml;&ouml;andjal &otilde;igust k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatu kohta antud k&uuml;simuses otsust teha. </eesti>
<inglise>During the specified time the employer does not have the right to make a decision on the given issue concerning the provisions of subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Informeerimise ja konsulteerimise korras ja sageduses lepivad t&ouml;&ouml;andja ja ameti&uuml;hing kokku. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Employers and trade unions shall agree upon the procedure for and frequency of informing and consulting. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Ameti&uuml;hingu ja selle valitud esindajate &otilde;iguste kaitse asutuse, organisatsiooni ja &uuml;hingu &uuml;hinemisel, jagunemisel, &uuml;mberkujundamisel, ettev&otilde;tte v&otilde;i selle osa &uuml;lemineku korral </eesti>
<inglise>Protection of rights of trade unions and their elected members upon merger, division and transformation of agencies, organisations and companies, or upon transfer of enterprises or parts thereof </inglise>
<eesti>Ameti&uuml;hingu ja selle valitud esindajate &otilde;igused ja kohustused t&ouml;&ouml;andja suhtes ei muutu t&ouml;&ouml;andja &otilde;iguste ja kohustuste &uuml;lemineku korral. </eesti>
<inglise>The rights and obligations of trade unions and their elected representatives do not change in respect of employers upon transfer of the rights and obligations of the employers. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Ameti&uuml;hingute p&auml;devus t&ouml;&ouml;alaste seaduste ja s&otilde;lmitud lepingute t&auml;itmise &uuml;le kontrolli teostamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Competence of trade unions upon exercise of supervision over compliance with labour laws and performance of contracts </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja rikub t&ouml;&ouml;- ja teenistusalaseid seadusi, t&ouml;&ouml;- ja kollektiivlepingut ning ameti&uuml;hingu liikmete huve puudutavaid muid lepinguid, on ameti&uuml;hingul &otilde;igus p&ouml;&ouml;rduda T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni ja teiste j&auml;relevalveasutuste poole. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If an employer violates labour laws or laws regulating public service, an employment contract or collective agreement or other contracts concerning the interests of the members of a trade union, the trade union has the right of recourse to the Labour Inspectorate and other supervisory agencies. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relevalveasutusel on kohustus vastata kirjalikule p&ouml;&ouml;rdumisele hiljemalt kahe n&auml;dala jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>A supervisory agency is required to reply to a written appeal not later than within two weeks. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;i tema esindaja seadust v&otilde;i lepingut ei t&auml;ida v&otilde;i seda rikub, on ameti&uuml;hingul, kelle liige t&ouml;&ouml;taja on, &otilde;igus t&ouml;&ouml;taja vastava p&ouml;&ouml;rdumise korral n&otilde;uda t&ouml;&ouml;andjalt seaduse v&otilde;i lepingu t&auml;itmist v&otilde;i rikkumise l&otilde;petamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If an employer or a representative of an employer does not comply with law or fails to perform or violates a contract, the trade union a member of which the employee is has the right to demand that the employer comply with law or perform the contract or terminate the violation at the corresponding request of the employee. </inglise>
<eesti>Ameti&uuml;hingu p&auml;devusse kuulub oma liikme vastava p&ouml;&ouml;rdumise korral t&ouml;&ouml;- ja kollektiivlepinguid, t&ouml;&ouml;tingimusi, t&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaega ning t&ouml;&ouml;re&zcaron;iimi, palgatingimusi, palga maksmise aluseid, t&ouml;&ouml;ohutust, sotsiaalkindlustuse makse v&otilde;i maksete tegemist puudutavate dokumentide kontrollimine. </eesti>
<inglise>At the corresponding request of a member of the trade union, the verification of employment contracts and collective agreements, documents concerning working conditions, working and rest time and work regimes, wage conditions, bases for payment of wages, occupational safety, social insurance payments or making of payments falls within the competence of the trade union. </inglise>
<eesti>6. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 6 </inglise>
<eesti>Vaidluste lahendamise kord ja vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for Dispute Resolution, Liability </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Vaidluste lahendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Dispute resolution </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse s&auml;tete kohaldamisel tekkinud individuaalsed t&ouml;&ouml;vaidlused t&ouml;&ouml;tajate v&otilde;i ameti&uuml;hingu valitud esindajate ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja vahel lahendatakse individuaalsete t&ouml;&ouml;vaidluste lahendamise korras ning avalikus teenistuses tekkinud vaidlused lahendatakse halduskohtumenetluse seadustikus (RT I 1999, 31, 425; 33, &otilde;iend; 40, &otilde;iend; 96, 846; 2000, 51, 321) s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Individual labour disputes between employees or elected members of a trade union and an employer arising in the application of provisions of this Act shall be resolved pursuant to the procedure for the resolution of individual labour disputes; disputes arising in public service shall be resolved pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Code of Administrative Court Procedure (RT I 1999, 31, 425; 33, correction notice; 40, correction notice; 96, 846; 2000, 51, 321). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seadusega s&auml;tete kohaldamisel tekkinud muud vaidlused lahendatakse kohtu korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Other disputes arising from application of provisions of this Act shall be resolved by a court. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Liability </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse rikkumise eest kannavad f&uuml;&uuml;silised isikud distsiplinaar-, tsiviil-, haldus- ja kriminaalvastutust, juriidilised isikud tsiviilvastutust seadusega etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Natural persons shall bear, pursuant to the procedure provided by law, disciplinary, civil, administrative or criminal liability and legal persons shall bear civil liability for violation of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ameti&uuml;hingul, mille &otilde;igusi rikuti, on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda rikkumise l&otilde;petamist, kohustuse t&auml;itmist ning tekitatud varalise ja mittevaralise kahju h&uuml;vitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A trade union the rights of which are violated has the right to demand termination of the violation, performance of obligations and compensation for the proprietary and non-proprietary damage caused through the violation. </inglise>
<eesti>7. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 7 </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse rakendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Implementation of Act </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse kohaldamine ameti&uuml;hingutele </eesti>
<inglise>Application of this Act to trade unions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Alates k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisest v&otilde;ib ameti&uuml;hinguid asutada ainult k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud korras ja neile kohaldatakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) As of entry into force of this Act, trade unions shall be founded only pursuant to the procedure provided for in this Act and the provisions of this Act apply to trade unions. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist asutatud ning mittetulundus&uuml;hingute ja sihtasutuste registrisse kantud ameti&uuml;hingu kannab registripidaja, l&auml;htudes ameti&uuml;hingu nimest v&otilde;i p&otilde;hikirjas s&auml;testatud eesm&auml;rgist, mittetulundus&uuml;hingute ja sihtasutuste registri allosana peetavasse ameti&uuml;hingute registrisse kuue kuu jooksul k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A registrar shall, within six months as of entry into force of this Act, enter a trade union founded before the entry into force of this Act and entered in the non-profit associations and foundations register, based on the name of the trade union or the objective provided for in the articles of association, in the register of trade unions which is maintained as part of the non-profit associations and foundations register. </inglise>
<eesti>Registripidaja teatab vastavale ameti&uuml;hingule kandeotsusest. </eesti>
<inglise>The registrar shall notify the corresponding trade union of the entry order. </inglise>
<eesti>Mittetulundus&uuml;hingute ja sihtasutuste registrisse kantud ameti&uuml;hingul, mis ei ole kantud ameti&uuml;hingute registrisse, on &otilde;igus taotleda registrisse kandmist. </eesti>
<inglise>A trade union which is entered in the non-profit associations and foundations register and is not entered in the register of trade unions has the right to apply for entry in the register of trade unions. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ameti&uuml;hingul, mis oli asutatud ENSV ameti&uuml;hingute seaduse (ENSV Teataja 1989, 40, 623; RT 1992, 35, 462) alusel ja ei olnud &uuml;mber registreeritud mittetulundus&uuml;hingute seaduse (RT I 1996, 42, 811; 1998, 96, 1515; 1999, 10, 155; 23, 355; 67, 658) alusel, on &otilde;igus taotleda registrisse kandmist asutamisdokumentide alusel, kui selle p&otilde;hikiri ei ole vastuolus k&auml;esoleva seaduse n&otilde;uetega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A trade union which is founded pursuant to Estonian SSR Trade Unions Act (ENSV Teataja (3) 1989, 40, 623; RT 1992, 35, 462) and is not re-registered pursuant to the Non-profit Associations Act (RT I 1996, 42, 811; 1998, 96, 1515; 1999, 10, 155; 23, 355; 67, 658) has the right to apply for entry in the register of trade unions on the basis of foundation documents if the articles of association thereof are not contrary to the requirements of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Ameti&uuml;hingul, mis ei olnud &uuml;mber registreeritud mittetulundus&uuml;hingute seaduse alusel, on &otilde;igus taotleda registrisse kandmist kuue kuu jooksul k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>A trade union which is not re-registered pursuant to the Non-profit Associations Act has the right to apply for entry in the register within six months as of entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Registrisse kandmise avalduses tuleb m&auml;rkida seaduses s&auml;testatud andmed, avaldusele tuleb lisada seaduses s&auml;testatud dokumendid, v&auml;lja arvatud asutamisleping, samuti ettev&otilde;tte registris registreerimise tunnistus. </eesti>
<inglise>An application for entry in the register shall set out the information as provided by law, and the documents provided by law, except the memorandum of association, and the certificate of registration of the enterprise in the register shall be appended to the application. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ettev&otilde;tte t&ouml;&ouml;tajate hulgast valitud ameti&uuml;hingu esindajale antakse p&auml;rast tema volituste l&otilde;ppemist valitaval ametikohal tagasi endine t&ouml;&ouml; v&otilde;i amet, selle puudumisel teine samav&auml;&auml;rne t&ouml;&ouml;- v&otilde;i ametikoht. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) After termination of authority in the elected position, a representative of a trade union elected from among the employees of an enterprise shall be reinstated in his or her former job or position, and where such position no longer exists, in another equivalent job or position. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigil&otilde;ivuseaduses tehtav muudatus </eesti>
<inglise>Amendments to State Fees Act </inglise>
<eesti>Riigil&otilde;ivuseaduse (RT I 1997, 80, 1344; 2000, 5, 32; 10, 58; 19, 117; 26, 150; 29, 168 ja 169; 39, 237; 49, 300; 54, 346 ja 349) &sect; 18 t&auml;iendatakse l&otilde;ikega 2 (1) j&auml;rgmises s&otilde;nastuses: </eesti>
<inglise>Section 18 of the State Fees Act (RT I 1997, 80, 1344; 2000, 5, 32; 10, 58; 19, 117; 26, 150; 29, 168 and 169; 39, 237; 49, 300; 54, 346 and 349) is amended by adding subsection (2 (1)) worded as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>"(2 (1)) Riigil&otilde;ivuga ei maksustata ameti&uuml;hingute mittetulundus&uuml;hingute ja sihtasutuste registri kandeid." </eesti>
<inglise>"(2 (1)) A state fee is not imposed on the register entries of non-profit associations and foundations of trade unions." </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>Kollektiivlepingu seaduses tehtavad muudatused </eesti>
<inglise>Amendments to Collective Agreements Act </inglise>
<eesti>Kollektiivlepingu seaduses (RT I 1993, 20, 353; 1999, 60, 616) tehakse j&auml;rgmised muudatused: </eesti>
<inglise>The Collective Agreements Act (RT I 1993, 20, 353; 1999, 60, 616) is amended as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) paragrahvi 3 t&auml;iendatakse l&otilde;ikega 3 j&auml;rgmises s&otilde;nastuses: </eesti>
<inglise>1) subsection (3) is added to &sect; 3 worded as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>"(3) Ettev&otilde;ttes, asutuses ja muus organisatsioonis s&otilde;lmib kollektiivlepinguid t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hing. </eesti>
<inglise>"(3) Collective agreements in enterprises, agencies and other organisations shall be entered into by unions of employees. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui ettev&otilde;ttes, asutuses v&otilde;i muus organisatsioonis ei esinda t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid ameti&uuml;hing, s&otilde;lmib kollektiivlepingu t&ouml;&ouml;tajate volitatud esindaja. </eesti>
<inglise>If employees are not represented by a trade union in an enterprise, agency or other organisation, an authorised representative of the employees shall enter into the collective agreement. </inglise>
