<eesti>2) paragrahvi 4 t&auml;iendatakse l&otilde;igetega 4 ja 5 j&auml;rgmises s&otilde;nastuses: </eesti>
<inglise>2) subsections (4) and (5) are added to &sect; 4 worded as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>"(4) T&ouml;&ouml;andjate &uuml;hingu v&otilde;i liidu ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;hingu v&otilde;i liidu ning t&ouml;&ouml;andjate keskliidu ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate keskliidu vahel s&otilde;lmitud kollektiivlepingut v&otilde;ib laiendada poolte kokkuleppel k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 6 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1 ja 3 m&auml;&auml;ratud tingimuste osas. </eesti>
<inglise>"(4) A collective agreement entered into between an association or federation of employers and a union or federation of employees and a collective agreement entered into between the central federation of employers and the central federation employees may be extended by agreement of the parties in respect of the conditions determined in clauses 6 (1) 1) and 3) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Laienemise ulatus m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks kollektiivlepingus. </eesti>
<inglise>The scope of extension shall be determined in the collective agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Laiendatud kollektiivlepingute tingimused avaldatakse sotsiaalministri poolt ametlikus v&auml;ljaandes Ametlikud Teadaanded. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The terms and conditions of extended collective agreements shall be published by the Minister of Social Affairs in the official publication Ametlikud Teadaanded (2). </inglise>
<eesti>Laiendatud kollektiivlepingute tingimused j&otilde;ustuvad teadaande avaldamisele j&auml;rgneval p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>The terms and conditions of extended collective agreements enter into force on the day following publication of the notice. </inglise>
<eesti>&ldquo;; </eesti>
<inglise>&ldquo;; </inglise>
